**Week 3 Internship Summary**

During my third week of internship, I focused primarily on developing a C# Windows Forms application integrated with biometric functionality using an SDK. This involved understanding how to connect the biometric device to the system, handling data capture, and ensuring proper interaction between the hardware and the software interface.

In addition to development work, I gained basic knowledge of networking concepts, specifically the differences and applications of WAN (Wide Area Network) and LAN (Local Area Network). This helped me better understand how systems communicate within and outside an organization.

Lastly, I was introduced to the fundamentals of automation engineering. Although still at a beginner level, I learned how automation can improve efficiency in systems and processes, and how it can be applied in real-world scenarios.

Overall, Week 3 enhanced both my technical development skills and my understanding of networking and automation concepts.
